22/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- OSCE's chairman-in-office, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, said during a visit to Tirana Thursday (21 October) that the OSCE plans to progressively reduce its presence in Macedonia, Kosovo and Serbia-Montenegro because of improvement in their electoral systems. Passy met with Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami, Prime Minister Fatos Nano and Albanian President Alfred Moisiu. Talks focused on Albania's election law, regional co-operation and the progress of joint infrastructural projects such as Transport Corridor 8. (Albanian News, 24 Chasa, Trud - 22/10/04)
